  "text": "In the present survey, girls did not show a higher caries experience than boys, which is common [CITATION_1] . Only an age effect for D 2 MF 2 -S was observed. Despite the 1-year age difference, 7-year-old children had more carious lesions in permanent teeth than children aged 6. This finding showed once more that erupting and just-erupted permanent molars are vulnerable to carious lesion development [CITATION_2] .",
